(40, 8, 15, 40, 9, 20, 20, 'touched her hand', 'Healing Touch Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of touching as a means of healing. In Matthew 8:15, Jesus touches the hand of a woman to heal her, while in Matthew 9:20, a woman touches the hem of his garment for healing.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 15, 43, 12, 1, 3, 'ministered unto them', 'Service After Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of service following healing. In Matthew, the healed woman immediately serves Jesus and his disciples, while in John, Martha serves Jesus after Lazarus''s resurrection.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 16, 2, 15, 26, 26, NULL, 'Healing and Deliverance Theme', 'Both passages emphasize healing and deliverance from affliction. Matthew 8:16 speaks of Jesus healing the sick and casting out spirits, while Exodus 15:26 promises that God will not bring diseases upon those who follow His commandments.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
