(40, 8, 18, 40, 14, 22, 22, 'depart unto the other side', 'Departure to the Other Side', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' command to depart to the other side, indicating a deliberate movement across water. This connection highlights the continuity of Jesus'' ministry and his interactions with the multitudes.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 18, 40, 8, 1, 1, 'great multitudes', 'Jesus and the Multitudes', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of great multitudes following Jesus. The first passage shows Jesus commanding departure due to the multitude''s presence, while the second illustrates their following him down from the mountain.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 18, 41, 1, 35, 38, 'depart unto the other side', 'Jesus'' Movement and Mission', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' intention to move to new locations to preach. In Matthew, he commands to depart, while in Mark, he expresses the need to go to the next towns for preaching.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 19, 42, 22, 33, 34, 'I will follow thee whithersoever thou goest', 'Commitment to Follow Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of commitment to follow Jesus, as seen in both passages. The scribe expresses a willingness to follow Jesus anywhere, while Peter asserts his readiness to accompany Jesus even to death.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
